QUESTION NO: 1
SVC (SAN Volume Controller) can provide which of the following?
A. Can provision storage but has to take the client down to do it.
B. Can increase performance by using the EMC pass through driver.
C. Reduce Storage costs.
D. Apply Time Finder to different vendors disk sub-systems.
Answer: C
Reference: http://www-03.ibm.com/systems/uk/storage/software/virtualization/svc/ (see the
heading in grey)
QUESTION NO: 2
Which feature does TSM (Tivoli Storage Manager) NOT provide?
A. Backup and Recovery
B. Device mapping
C. Archive and Retrieve
D. HSM (Hierarchical Storage Manager)
E. Content management
Answer: E
Explanation: TSM is a storage manager and it does not provide content management. For
content management, IBM offers DB2 content manager or IBM content manager. Logically a
storage manager is not a content manager, it is a storage manager that provides device mapping,
backup and recovery, archive and retrieve and since TSM is an IBM product it has a flavor that
provides hierarchical storage manager called TSM HSM as described in the resource below:
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IBM_Tivoli_Storage_Manager
